  "texts": [
    "Since B is simply connected, we have [EL78, Par.",
    "4.8] that ( B,g B) = ( B′, g ′ B) × (F, g F) is a Riemannian product and η: ( B, g B) → ( B′, g ′ B)is the projection onto the first factor.",
    "Since T F = ker dh, (20b) implies (F, g F) is Einstein with Ric(g F) = -1 2 g F. Moreover, it is clear that (g ′ B, ρ ′, h ′) is a solution to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equation with h ′ totally geodesic and injective.",
    "Letting (M ′, g ′) be the Ricci soliton associated to (g ′ B, ρ ′, h ′) via Proposition 3.4, we see that( M, g) ≃ isom.",
    "( M ′, g′) × (F, g F).Since ( M ′, g′) is homogeneous, the result follows."
  ]
